<item>
            <title>[LU-3072] add more operations to racer</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3072</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Add chown(), truncate, ftruncate, some xattr setting to racer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;file_rename.sh should use &apos;mv -T&apos; as well as &apos;mv&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mknod() is not used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On my home setup I find that racer finds server-side bugs much faster if file_create.sh is modified to less IO per file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is some problem with running racer through autotest that needs to be understood.  It seems not to start at all.  Maybe someone knows what&apos;s going on and can comment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
